FIGURE 2.
Details of morphology of 

Epigomphus pechumani
:

a, male head, dorsal view; b, female head dorsal view; c, accessory genitalia, ventral view (posterior hamuli were moved back to observe anterior hamuli); d, segments 2–4 of vesica spermalis, right lateral view; e, female hind leg, lateral view; f, male hind leg, lateral view; g, male anterior leg, lateral view. 
ah
= anterior hamule; 
co
= cornua; 
h
= horns; 
lb
= lateral lobe; 
ph
= posterior hamule; 
prp
= prepuce; 
ps
= peg-like spines; 
ss
= scale-like spines; 
vs
= vesica spermalis; 
v2–4
= segments of vesica spermalis. (Figs. e-g by M. Astudillo).

