; a–d male S10 and caudal appendages: a, ventrolateral view; b, dorsomedial view; c, dorsal view; d, posterior view; e–g female S9–10: e, vulvar lamina, ventral view; f, left lateral view of caudal appendages; g right lateral view of caudal appendages. 
asp
= apical spine; 
bvt
= baso-ventral tooth; 
bit
= baso-internal tooth; 
Ce
= cercus; 
dc
= dorsal concavity; 
Ep
= epiproct; 
n
= notch; 
sat
